       "description": "Build the Team Week manager dashboard per PRD §10, §20.\n\n**TeamWeekPage component:**\n- Team selector (for managers with multiple teams) and week selector.\n- Tabbed or sectioned layout with all dashboard sections.\n\n**OverviewSection:**\n- Compliance cards: lock compliance (X/Y locked, % on-time), reconcile compliance (X/Y reconciled, % on-time).\n- Points summary: total planned points, total achieved points, delta.\n- Open exceptions count with severity breakdown.\n\n**ByPersonSection:**\n- Table/list of direct reports with columns: name, plan state, points committed/budget, chess piece summary (icons), risk flags (icons), carry-forward streak count, major post-lock changes indicator.\n- Expandable rows to show individual commit lists.\n- Click through to view full plan detail for a direct report.\n\n**ByRcdoSection:**\n- Tree or grouped table: Rally Cry → DO → Outcome with planned points, achieved points, commit count per branch.\n- Coverage gap highlighting: RCDOs with no commits shown distinctly.\n- Planned vs achieved bar per branch.\n\n**ChessDistributionSection:**\n- Stacked bar or pie chart: team's commit and point distribution across King/Queen/Rook/Bishop/Knight/Pawn.\n- Highlight concentration of critical work (King/Queen allocation).\n\n**UncommittedWorkSection:**\n- Two sub-lists: assigned tickets with no linked commit; unassigned tickets targeted to the week.\n- Ticket details: key, title, assignee (or 'Unassigned'), status, target week.\n- Quick-assign action for unassigned tickets.\n\n**ExceptionQueueSection:**\n- Filterable list of exceptions sorted by severity (King/Queen first).\n- Exception types: missed lock, missed reconcile, over-budget, added/changed King after lock, repeated carry-forward, high scope volatility.\n- Each exception shows: user, type, detail, created date, resolution status.\n- Resolve action: mark as reviewed with optional note.\n- Comment action: add plan-level or commit-level comment.\n\n**Component tests:** overview cards compute correct aggregates, by-person table renders direct reports, RCDO rollup groups correctly, chess distribution renders accurately, uncommitted work shows correct tickets without double-counting, exception queue sorts by severity, resolve and comment actions work.",
