+      "title": "Backend ticket and supplementary API contract alignment",
+      "description": "The step-14 frontend (Tickets UI, PlanHistoryView, CarryForwardLineageView, TeamHistoryView, FilterBar) was built against API shapes the backend does not yet provide. This step adds every missing backend endpoint and aligns every existing DTO so the frontend can function at runtime.\n\n## Contract gap analysis (all gaps resolved in this step):\n\n### 1. Add ticket priority field\n- **Gap**: Frontend sends/expects `priority` (CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW); backend WorkItem entity & DB have no priority column.\n- **Fix**: Create Flyway migration `V3__add_ticket_priority.sql`: `ALTER TABLE work_item ADD COLUMN priority TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'MEDIUM' CHECK (priority IN ('CRITICAL','HIGH','MEDIUM','LOW'));` Add index `idx_work_item_priority`.\n- Create Java enum `TicketPriority` (CRITICAL, HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW) in `domain/enums/`.\n- Add `priority` field to `WorkItem` entity with `@Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)`, default MEDIUM.\n- Add `priority` to `CreateTicketRequest`, `UpdateTicketRequest`, and `TicketResponse` records.\n- Update `TicketService.createTicket()` and `updateTicket()` to handle priority.\n\n### 2. Paginated, filterable, sortable ticket list\n- **Gap**: Frontend calls `GET /api/tickets?status=&assigneeUserId=&teamId=&rcdoNodeId=&targetWeek=&priority=&page=&pageSize=&sortBy=&sortDir=` expecting `PagedTicketResponse { items, total, page, pageSize }`. Backend returns unpaginated `List<TicketResponse>` filtered only by teamId.\n- **Fix**: Create `TicketListParams` value object for all filter criteria. Create `PagedTicketResponse` Java record: `{ List<TicketSummaryResponse> items, long total, int page, int pageSize }`. Create `TicketSummaryResponse` record (compact: id, key, title, status, priority, assigneeUserId, teamId, rcdoNodeId, estimatePoints, targetWeekStartDate, createdAt, updatedAt — no nested objects).\n- Add `WorkItemRepository` method using Spring Data `Specification<WorkItem>` or `@Query` with dynamic filtering + `Pageable`. All filter params optional.\n- Refactor `TicketController.listTickets()` to accept all query params (all optional, including teamId) and return `PagedTicketResponse`. Default page=1, pageSize=20. Support sortBy: key, title, status, priority, updatedAt; sortDir: asc/desc.\n\n### 3. Enriched ticket detail response\n- **Gap**: Frontend `TicketResponse` interface expects `statusHistory: TicketStatusHistory[]` and `linkedCommits: LinkedCommitEntry[]` embedded. Backend `TicketResponse` is flat.\n- **Fix**: Create `TicketDetailResponse` record containing all fields of current `TicketResponse` plus `priority`, `List<TicketStatusHistoryResponse> statusHistory`, `List<LinkedCommitEntry> linkedCommits`. Create `LinkedCommitEntry` record: commitId, planId, commitTitle, chessPiece, estimatePoints, weekStartDate, outcome.\n- Update `TicketController.getTicket()` to return `TicketDetailResponse`. Add `WeeklyCommitRepository.findByWorkItemId()` to query linked commits. Assemble the enriched response in `TicketService.getTicketDetail()`.\n\n### 4. Ticket summaries endpoint\n- **Gap**: Frontend calls `GET /api/tickets/summaries?teamId=` for commit-linking picklists; no backend endpoint.\n- **Fix**: Add `GET /api/tickets/summaries` to `TicketController`. Returns `List<TicketSummaryResponse>` (compact, no pagination — used for dropdowns). Optional teamId filter.\n\n### 5. Create ticket from commit\n- **Gap**: Frontend calls `POST /api/tickets/from-commit` with `{ commitId, planId, ...overrides }`; no backend endpoint.\n- **Fix**: Add `POST /api/tickets/from-commit` to `TicketController`. Create `CreateTicketFromCommitRequest` record (commitId, planId, optional override fields). Service method looks up commit + plan, copies title/description/RCDO/estimate/team to a new WorkItem, applies any overrides, saves, and returns `TicketDetailResponse`.\n\n### 6. Plan history endpoint\n- **Gap**: Frontend calls `GET /api/users/{userId}/plan-history`; no backend endpoint.\n- **Fix**: Add `PlanHistoryController` (or add to `PlanController`). Endpoint: `GET /api/users/{userId}/plan-history`. Create `WeeklyPlanHistoryEntry` record: planId, weekStartDate, planState, compliant, commitCount, plannedPoints, achievedPoints, carryForwardCount. Service queries all plans for user ordered by weekStartDate desc, computes aggregates from commits.\n\n### 7. Team history endpoint\n- **Gap**: Frontend calls `GET /api/teams/{teamId}/history`; no backend endpoint.\n- **Fix**: Add `GET /api/teams/{teamId}/history` to `TeamController`. Create `TeamHistoryResponse` record: teamId, `List<TeamWeekHistoryEntry>`. `TeamWeekHistoryEntry`: weekStartDate, memberCount, complianceRate, plannedPoints, achievedPoints, carryForwardRate, exceptionCount. Service aggregates per-week data across team members over recent weeks (default last 12 weeks).\n\n### 8. Carry-forward lineage URL and response shape alignment\n- **Gap**: Frontend calls `GET /api/commits/{commitId}/carry-forward-lineage` expecting `{ currentCommitId, chain: CarryForwardNode[] }` where each node has commitId, planId, weekStartDate, title, outcome, streak. Backend serves `/api/commits/{commitId}/lineage` returning `{ rootCommitId, chain: CarryForwardLinkResponse[] }`.\n- **Fix**: Add alias route `GET /api/commits/{commitId}/carry-forward-lineage` in `CarryForwardController` pointing to same handler. Create `CarryForwardNodeResponse` record matching frontend's `CarryForwardNode` shape (commitId, planId, weekStartDate, title, outcome, streak). Update or add a new method in `CarryForwardService` that returns `{ currentCommitId: UUID, chain: List<CarryForwardNodeResponse> }` using a new `CarryForwardLineageDetailResponse` record. Keep existing `/lineage` endpoint for backward compatibility.\n\n**Unit tests for all additions:**\n- Pagination: verify page/total/pageSize math, filter combinations, sort orderings, empty results.\n- Priority: create/update with all priority values, filter by priority, migration default.\n- Enriched detail: status history and linked commits populated correctly.\n- Summaries: returns compact list filtered by team.\n- From-commit: copies fields correctly, applies overrides, handles missing commit.\n- Plan history: aggregates correct per-week stats, ordered newest-first.\n- Team history: compliance/points/CF rates computed correctly.\n- Lineage alias: both URL paths return same data, response shape matches frontend expectations.",
