-      "description": "Implement the AI foundation and commit-level assistance per PRD §17 (capabilities 1-3).\n\n**AI provider abstraction (backend):**\n- `AiProvider` interface: `generateSuggestion(context: AiContext): Promise<AiSuggestionResult>`. Context includes commit data, plan data, RCDO tree, historical patterns.\n- `AiProviderRegistry`: registers providers, selects active provider. Supports disabling AI entirely via feature flag.\n- Graceful degradation: if provider unavailable or disabled, all AI endpoints return empty suggestions with `aiAvailable: false` flag. Core workflow unaffected.\n- Default implementation: stub provider for development; production provider pluggable.\n\n**AI suggestion storage:**\n- `AiSuggestion` records: id, userId, suggestionType, context hash, suggestion payload, rationale text, modelVersion, createdAt.\n- `AiFeedback` records: suggestionId, action (ACCEPTED, DISMISSED, EDITED), timestamp.\n- Every suggestion stores rationale explaining why it was generated.\n\n**Commit drafting assistance (capability 1):**\n- `POST /api/ai/commit-draft-assist`: given commit title/description, returns suggestions for: improved title wording, concise description, success criteria (especially for King/Queen), estimate points based on similar past commits.\n- Suggestions returned as editable proposals, never auto-applied.\n- Frontend integration: 'AI Assist' button on CommitForm. Shows suggestion panel with accept/edit/dismiss per suggestion.\n\n**Commit quality linting (capability 2):**\n- `POST /api/ai/commit-lint`: given plan with all commits, returns lint results.\n- Checks: vague titles (too short, too generic), missing success criteria for King/Queen, parent-level RCDO linkage when leaf exists, duplicate/near-duplicate titles, estimate inconsistency (similar work different estimates), over-fragmented plan (>8 commits).\n- Results clearly separated into: `hardValidation` (blocks lock, same as lock validation) and `softGuidance` (AI suggestions, informational only).\n- Frontend integration: AI Lint Panel on My Week page. Shows lint results with severity icons. Runs on save and pre-lock.\n\n**RCDO link suggestions (capability 3):**\n- `POST /api/ai/rcdo-suggest`: given commit text and optional ticket data, suggests primary RCDO with confidence score and rationale.\n- Only surface suggestions above confidence threshold (configurable, default 0.7).\n- Rationale examples: 'keyword match with Outcome X', 'linked ticket is tagged to Outcome Y', 'similar commit last week linked to Outcome Z'.\n- Never auto-link. Frontend shows suggestion with accept/dismiss in RCDO selector.\n\n**Unit tests:** provider abstraction with graceful degradation, suggestion storage and retrieval, feedback recording, draft assistance returns structured suggestions, lint distinguishes hard vs soft, RCDO suggestion respects confidence threshold, AI unavailable doesn't break workflows, rationale attached to every suggestion.",
