       "description": "Implement cadence configuration and admin settings per PRD §13 FR-10.\n\n**Configuration model:**\n- `OrgConfig` table: orgId, default week cadence fields (weekStartDay, draftOpenOffset, lockDueOffset, reconcileOpenOffset, reconcileDueOffset), defaultWeeklyBudget, timezone.\n- `TeamConfigOverride` table: teamId, overridden cadence fields (null = use org default), timezone override.\n- `CapacityOverride` (already exists from step 8): per-user per-week override.\n\n**ConfigurationService:**\n- `getEffectiveConfig(teamId)`: merges org defaults with team overrides. Returns resolved cadence deadlines for any given week.\n- `getEffectiveCapacity(userId, weekStart)`: returns user capacity (override > team default > org default, default 10).\n- `updateOrgConfig(config)`: admin-only.\n- `updateTeamConfig(teamId, overrides)`: admin or team manager.\n- Default cadence per PRD §12: planning week Mon-Fri, draft opens Friday 12:00, reconcile opens Friday 17:00, reconcile due Monday 10:00, lock due Monday 12:00.\n\n**Integration with lifecycle services:**\n- Auto-lock job reads effective config to determine cutoff time per team.\n- Reconcile-open job reads effective config to determine transition time.\n- Plan creation uses effective capacity for budget snapshot.\n\n**Admin settings UI (frontend):**\n- Admin-only page (accessible from a settings gear icon for Admin role).\n- Org-level config form: week start day, deadline offsets, default budget.\n- Team-level overrides: list of teams with override indicators, edit form per team.\n- Per-user capacity overrides: searchable user list with current/override capacity display.\n\n**REST endpoints:**\n- `GET /api/config/org` — org config\n- `PUT /api/config/org` — update org config (admin only)\n- `GET /api/config/teams/{id}` — team config with effective values\n- `PUT /api/config/teams/{id}` — update team override\n- `GET /api/config/capacity/{userId}?week=` — effective capacity\n\n**Unit tests:** effective config merges org + team correctly, capacity resolution chain (override > team > org > default), lifecycle jobs use per-team deadlines, admin-only access enforced, config changes don't affect already-locked plans.",
