       "description": "Implement comprehensive audit logging (PRD §13 FR-11), accessibility (PRD §24), and final integration polish.\n\n**Audit logging (backend):**\n- `AuditLogService`: records all auditable events with actor, action, target, timestamp, before/after payload.\n- Auditable events: plan state transitions (create, lock, auto-lock, reconcile-open, reconcile-submit), commit CRUD, scope change events, carry-forward actions, RCDO create/update/archive/move, ticket status changes, capacity overrides, manager comments, AI suggestion create/feedback, admin config changes.\n- `audit_log` table: id, actorId, actorRole, action enum, targetType, targetId, beforePayload (JSON), afterPayload (JSON), timestamp, ipAddress.\n- Audit records are append-only and immutable.\n- `GET /api/audit-log?targetType=&targetId=&actorId=&action=&from=&to=` — query audit log (admin only, or scoped to own actions for IC/manager).\n\n**Snapshot immutability verification:**\n- Add integrity checks: lock snapshots and reconcile snapshots cannot be modified after creation.\n- Database-level: no UPDATE/DELETE permissions on snapshot tables for application user (or application-level write-once enforcement).\n\n**Idempotency verification:**\n- Review all lifecycle jobs (auto-lock, reconcile-open, read-model refresh) for idempotency.\n- Add guards: check current state before transition, use optimistic locking, verify no duplicate snapshots or carry-forward links on retry.\n\n**Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA):**\n- Keyboard navigation: all interactive elements focusable and operable via keyboard.\n- Commit reorder: ensure keyboard alternative (move-up/move-down buttons) works correctly with screen readers.\n- ARIA labels on all icon-only buttons, status badges, and interactive elements.\n- Color independence: chess piece types, plan states, risk flags, and outcomes distinguishable without color alone (icons, text labels, patterns).\n- Focus management: modal dialogs trap focus, return focus on close.\n- Form error announcements: validation errors announced to screen readers.\n\n**Integration verification:**\n- End-to-end flow tests (unit test level): create plan → add commits → lock → scope change → reconcile → carry-forward. Verify snapshots, events, and state transitions.\n- Verify permission boundaries: IC cannot access other's plans, peer sees only basic detail, manager sees full detail for directs.\n- Verify AI degradation: disable AI provider, confirm all core flows complete successfully.\n- Performance spot-checks: verify derived read model queries are used for dashboard endpoints.\n\n**Unit tests:** audit log records all event types with correct payloads, snapshot immutability enforced, lifecycle job idempotency (double-run produces no duplicates), accessibility attributes present on key components, end-to-end flow produces correct state transitions and snapshots, permission boundaries enforced.",
