-      "description": "Implement the notifications system per PRD §18.\n\n**Backend NotificationService:**\n- `NotificationEvent` enum covering all default events: DRAFT_WINDOW_OPENED, LOCK_DUE_REMINDER, AUTO_LOCK_OCCURRED, RECONCILIATION_OPENED, RECONCILIATION_DUE_REMINDER, REPEATED_CARRY_FORWARD_REMINDER, MANAGER_EXCEPTION_DIGEST, UNASSIGNED_TICKET_CREATED, CRITICAL_TICKET_BLOCKED.\n- `createNotification(userId, event, payload, priority)`: stores notification in DB.\n- Priority behavior: KING_EXCEPTION → immediate (high priority), QUEEN_ROOK_EXCEPTION → same-day digest (medium), BISHOP_KNIGHT_PAWN → daily digest (low).\n- Frequency controls: max 2 direct reminders per user per task per day. Low-priority batched into daily digest.\n- Business hours check: respect team local time.\n\n**Notification triggers (integrated into lifecycle services):**\n- Hook into auto-lock job → AUTO_LOCK_OCCURRED notification to user + MANAGER_EXCEPTION_DIGEST to manager.\n- Hook into reconcile-open job → RECONCILIATION_OPENED notification.\n- Hook into carry-forward → check streak, if >= 2 send REPEATED_CARRY_FORWARD_REMINDER.\n- Hook into scope change → if King changed, immediate MANAGER notification.\n- Hook into ticket status → if blocked and linked to King/Queen, CRITICAL_TICKET_BLOCKED.\n\n**NotificationDelivery tracking:**\n- Store delivery records: notificationId, channel (IN_APP, EMAIL), deliveredAt, readAt.\n- Mark-as-read endpoint.\n\n**Email digest preparation:**\n- `EmailDigestService`: aggregates pending notifications by user and priority. Prepares digest payload (actual email sending via host or external service — interface only in v1).\n\n**Frontend NotificationPanel:**\n- Bell icon in header with unread count badge.\n- Dropdown panel showing recent notifications grouped by priority.\n- Mark-as-read on click. Mark-all-read action.\n- Click notification to navigate to relevant resource (plan, commit, ticket, team view).\n\n**REST endpoints:**\n- `GET /api/notifications` — list user's notifications (paginated, filterable by read/unread)\n- `PUT /api/notifications/{id}/read` — mark as read\n- `PUT /api/notifications/read-all` — mark all as read\n\n**Unit tests:** notification creation with correct priority, frequency limiting (no >2 per task per day), lifecycle hook triggers correct events, delivery tracking records, digest aggregation groups correctly, frontend panel renders notifications, unread count badge updates.",
+      "title": "Frontend ticket contract alignment and Tickets UI completion",
+      "description": "Align all frontend types, API client, hooks, and components with the backend contracts established in step 14. The existing frontend Tickets UI components (TicketListView, TicketForm, TicketDetailView), history views (PlanHistoryView, CarryForwardLineageView, TeamHistoryView), and FilterBar were built against incorrect data shapes. This step fixes every mismatch so they function correctly at runtime.\n\n## Fixes applied:\n\n### 1. TicketStatus enum alignment\n- **Current**: `teamTypes.ts` defines `TicketStatus = 'TODO' | 'IN_PROGRESS' | 'DONE' | 'CANCELED' | 'BLOCKED'` (5 values). `ticketTypes.ts` re-exports it.\n- **Fix**: Change `TicketStatus` in `teamTypes.ts` to `'BACKLOG' | 'READY' | 'IN_PROGRESS' | 'BLOCKED' | 'DONE' | 'CANCELED'` (6 values, matching backend enum and shared package).\n- Update `TICKET_STATUS_LABELS`: add `BACKLOG: 'Backlog'`, `READY: 'Ready'`; remove `TODO`.\n- Update `TICKET_STATUS_TRANSITIONS` to match backend's transition map: `BACKLOG → [READY, IN_PROGRESS, CANCELED]`, `READY → [IN_PROGRESS, BACKLOG, CANCELED]`, `IN_PROGRESS → [DONE, BLOCKED, READY, CANCELED]`, `BLOCKED → [IN_PROGRESS, CANCELED]`, `DONE → []`, `CANCELED → []`.\n- Add `BACKLOG` and `READY` entries to `STATUS_BADGE_STYLES` in TicketListView and `STATUS_COLORS` in TicketDetailView.\n\n### 2. TicketForm status and default alignment\n- **Current**: TicketForm defaults status to `'TODO'` and offers 5 statuses.\n- **Fix**: Default to `'BACKLOG'`. Update `TICKET_STATUSES` array to include all 6 values. Update the status `<select>` options.\n\n### 3. Status transition API call fix\n- **Current**: `Tickets.tsx` handles status transitions by calling `ticketApi.updateTicket(ticketId, { status: newStatus })`. Backend's `UpdateTicketRequest` has no `status` field (step 14 may or may not add it — but the proper endpoint is `PUT /api/tickets/{id}/status`).\n- **Fix**: Add a `transitionStatus(ticketId: string, newStatus: TicketStatus, changedByUserId: string)` method to the ticket API client that calls `PUT /api/tickets/${id}/status` with `{ status, changedByUserId }`. Update `Tickets.tsx` `handleStatusTransition` to use this new method instead of `updateTicket`, passing the current user ID from host context.\n\n### 4. Carry-forward lineage API URL and response mapping\n- **Current**: `ticketApi.ts` calls `GET /api/commits/{commitId}/carry-forward-lineage`. Frontend expects `{ currentCommitId, chain: CarryForwardNode[] }` where each node has `commitId, planId, weekStartDate, title, outcome, streak`.\n- **Fix**: URL now matches (backend step 14 adds the alias). Verify the `CarryForwardLineageResponse` and `CarryForwardNode` types in `ticketTypes.ts` match the new `CarryForwardLineageDetailResponse` from backend. If any field names differ, update the frontend types. The backend in step 14 is being built to match these frontend types.\n\n### 5. Update TicketForm CreateTicketPayload for backend alignment\n- **Current**: Frontend `CreateTicketPayload` sends `priority`, `status`, `reporterUserId` etc. Verify all field names match the updated backend `CreateTicketRequest` (which now has `priority` after step 14).\n- **Fix**: Ensure field name casing and optionality match. If backend uses `targetWeekStartDate` but frontend sends `targetWeekStartDate`, verify match. Same for `estimatePoints`. Add any missing fields.\n\n### 6. Update all test fixtures\n- **Current**: Test fixtures in `TicketsPage.test.tsx` use `status: 'TODO'` and the `TODO`-based transition map.\n- **Fix**: Update all `makeTicketSummary()` and `makeTicketDetail()` fixtures to use `'BACKLOG'` as the default status. Update transition tests to test `BACKLOG → [READY, IN_PROGRESS, CANCELED]` instead of `TODO → [IN_PROGRESS, CANCELED]`. Add tests for the `READY` status. Update `DONE` terminal status test (unchanged). Update filter status options to include BACKLOG and READY.\n\n### 7. Ensure PlanHistoryView, TeamHistoryView, CarryForwardLineageView components are wired\n- Verify these components (built in step 14 original) are importable from the Tickets route or accessible from My Week / Team Week pages as intended. If they are standalone components without route-level integration, add appropriate navigation hooks (e.g., plan history accessible from My Week page, team history from Team Week page, lineage from commit detail). This may involve adding sub-routes or tabs.\n\n**Component and integration tests:**\n- All existing TicketsPage tests updated and passing with corrected status values.\n- New test: BACKLOG and READY status badges render with correct styles.\n- New test: status transition uses dedicated API method (not updateTicket).\n- New test: filter bar shows all 6 status options.\n- Verify PlanHistoryView, TeamHistoryView, CarryForwardLineageView test suites still pass.\n- Verify typecheck passes (no stale type references to 'TODO').",
