-      "description": "Implement AI risk signals and reconciliation assistance per PRD §17 (capabilities 4-6).\n\n**Risk detection service (capability 4):**\n- `RiskDetectionService`: computes risk signals per plan.\n- Runs on plan lock and daily for LOCKED plans (background job).\n- v1 risk signals with rationale:\n  - Overcommit: committed points > budget AND > user's historical average completed points. Rationale: 'X points committed vs Y budget, historical average completion is Z points.'\n  - Undercommit: committed points < 50% of budget with no capacity override. Rationale: 'Only X of Y budget points committed.'\n  - Repeated carry-forward: commit has carry-forward streak >= 2. Rationale: 'This work has been carried forward N consecutive weeks from [original date].'\n  - Blocked critical: King/Queen commit linked to a ticket in BLOCKED status for >2 business days. Rationale: 'King commit [title] linked to blocked ticket [key] for N days.'\n  - Scope volatility: >3 scope change events on a locked plan. Rationale: 'N scope changes recorded since lock, including [summary].'\n- Risk signals stored in `ai_suggestion` table with type RISK_SIGNAL.\n- Exposed via `GET /api/plans/{id}/risk-signals`.\n\n**Reconciliation assistance (capability 5):**\n- `POST /api/ai/reconcile-assist`: given plan in RECONCILING state, returns:\n  - Likely outcomes for unlinked commits based on notes and activity patterns.\n  - Draft summary of what changed after lock (generated from scope change events).\n  - Carry-forward recommendations with rationale for incomplete work.\n- All suggestions are proposals requiring user acceptance.\n- Frontend integration: 'AI Assist' panel on ReconcilePage. Shows suggestions per commit and overall summary. Accept/edit/dismiss controls.\n\n**Manager summary (capability 6):**\n- `GET /api/teams/{id}/week/{weekStart}/ai-summary`: generates team summary citing:\n  - Top RCDO branches receiving effort (with commit/point counts).\n  - Unresolved exceptions (linked to exception queue items).\n  - Repeated carry-forward patterns (names and streaks).\n  - Critical blocked items (linked to tickets).\n- Summary must cite underlying objects (IDs/links), not be a black-box narrative.\n- Frontend: summary card at top of Team Week dashboard (collapsible, dismissible).\n\n**Frontend risk displays:**\n- Risk flag icons on commits and plans in My Week and Team Week.\n- Risk detail tooltip/popover showing rationale text.\n- Risk flags hidden from peers (only visible to plan owner and manager per privacy rules).\n\n**Unit tests:** each risk signal type computed correctly with rationale, daily risk job processes LOCKED plans, reconcile assistance produces structured suggestions, manager summary cites source objects, risk flags respect privacy (hidden from peers), AI down returns empty risk signals without error.",
+      "title": "AI provider abstraction, commit assistance, and risk detection",
+      "description": "Implement the AI foundation, commit-level assistance (PRD §17 capabilities 1-3), and risk/reconciliation assistance (capabilities 4-6). These are merged into one step because they share the provider abstraction, suggestion storage, and feedback infrastructure.\n\n**AI provider abstraction (backend):**\n- `AiProvider` interface: `generateSuggestion(context: AiContext): AiSuggestionResult`. Context includes commit data, plan data, RCDO tree, historical patterns.\n- `AiProviderRegistry`: registers providers, selects active provider. Supports disabling AI entirely via feature flag.\n- Graceful degradation: if provider unavailable or disabled, all AI endpoints return empty suggestions with `aiAvailable: false` flag. Core workflow unaffected.\n- Default implementation: stub provider for development; production provider pluggable.\n\n**AI suggestion and feedback storage:**\n- `AiSuggestion` records: id, userId, suggestionType, context hash, suggestion payload, rationale text, modelVersion, createdAt.\n- `AiFeedback` records: suggestionId, action (ACCEPTED, DISMISSED, EDITED), timestamp.\n- Every suggestion stores rationale explaining why it was generated.\n\n**Commit drafting assistance (capability 1):**\n- `POST /api/ai/commit-draft-assist`: returns suggestions for improved title, description, success criteria, estimate based on similar past commits. Suggestions are editable proposals, never auto-applied.\n- Frontend: 'AI Assist' button on CommitForm. Shows suggestion panel with accept/edit/dismiss per suggestion.\n\n**Commit quality linting (capability 2):**\n- `POST /api/ai/commit-lint`: returns lint results. Checks: vague titles, missing success criteria for King/Queen, parent-level RCDO when leaf exists, duplicate/near-duplicate titles, estimate inconsistency, over-fragmented plan.\n- Results separated into `hardValidation` (blocks lock) and `softGuidance` (informational only).\n- Frontend: AI Lint Panel on My Week page.\n\n**RCDO link suggestions (capability 3):**\n- `POST /api/ai/rcdo-suggest`: suggests primary RCDO with confidence score and rationale. Only surface above threshold (default 0.7). Never auto-link.\n- Frontend: suggestion with accept/dismiss in RCDO selector.\n\n**Risk detection (capability 4):**\n- `RiskDetectionService`: computes risk signals per plan on lock and daily for LOCKED plans.\n- v1 signals with rationale: overcommit, undercommit, repeated carry-forward (streak >= 2), blocked critical (King/Queen + BLOCKED ticket > 2 days), scope volatility (> 3 changes).\n- Stored in `ai_suggestion` table with type RISK_SIGNAL.\n- `GET /api/plans/{id}/risk-signals`. Frontend: risk flag icons on commits/plans with rationale tooltips. Hidden from peers.\n\n**Reconciliation assistance (capability 5):**\n- `POST /api/ai/reconcile-assist`: likely outcomes for unlinked commits, draft summary of changes, carry-forward recommendations.\n- Frontend: 'AI Assist' panel on ReconcilePage.\n\n**Manager summary (capability 6):**\n- `GET /api/teams/{id}/week/{weekStart}/ai-summary`: team summary citing top RCDO branches, unresolved exceptions, carry-forward patterns, critical blocked items. Must cite underlying objects.\n- Frontend: summary card at top of Team Week dashboard.\n\n**Unit tests:** provider graceful degradation, suggestion storage/retrieval, feedback recording, draft assistance structured suggestions, lint hard vs soft, RCDO confidence threshold, each risk signal type with rationale, daily risk job, reconcile assistance, manager summary cites sources, privacy (hidden from peers), AI down returns empty without error.",
